And we quickly learn to associate that morpheme with our supplier of milk, right?

So we call her when we need her -- "ma".

Now on a pure phonological level, that begins at sound, begins with an attack, an ictus.

"ma" and ends in a descending glide.

"ma" that's the way we speak, ictus plus glide.

